w.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09171745/C30-SDM-Collection-with-Bottle-1536x654.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09171745/C30-SDM-Collection-with-Bottle-696x296.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09171745/C30-SDM-Collection-with-Bottle-1068x455.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09171745/C30-SDM-Collection-with-Bottle-1920x818.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09171745/C30-SDM-Collection-with-Bottle-986x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb25 986w\"></p><h3>A No-Nonsense Laboratory</h3><p>NEVERSECOND is the brainchild of longtime endurance runner Bill Armstrong and sports nutritionist Asker Jeukendrup Ph.D. Armstrong sought Jeukendrup out while searching for adequate nutritional support for his personal physical demands. The two shared dissatisfactions over their perceived shortcomings of the sports nutrition market.</p><p>Jeukendrup felt that some drinks could detract from endurance performance, stating “it is highly probable that some of their fueling products are even hindering performance because their composition is not optimal or because they contain unnecessary ingredients. I’ve seen both scenarios cause severe gastrointestinal distress, cramping and incomplete fueling.”</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09171923/Lisa-Norden_N2-Sponsored-Athlete.jpeg\" alt=\"Lisa Norden NeverSecond Athlete\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/09171923/Lisa-Norden_N2-Sponsored-Athlete.jpeg 2000w,https://bikeru